    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1946-07-08T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1946-07-08T00:00:00-05:00" n="503"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d503">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">867N.01/7–946: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The British Prime Minister</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Attlee</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to President <persName type="to"
                            >Truman</persName>
                    </hi>
                    <note n="99" xml:id="d503fn99">Copy transmitted to Mr. Acheson by Lord
                        Inverchapel on July 9.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">top secret</hi>
                    </seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">[<placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">London</hi>
                        </placeName>,] <date calendar="gregorian" when="1946-07-08">8 July,
                            1946</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Personal and Top Secret. Many thanks for your telegram of July 6th [<hi
                        rend="italic">5th</hi>] and for action you have taken to expedite the
                    departure of your committee and their staff. We shall all here be ready for
                    discussions to begin on Friday next.</p>
                <p>I shall be delighted to see Ambassador Grady and Mr. Dorr upon their arrival and
                    have asked Averell<note n="1" xml:id="d503fn1">Ambassador Harriman.</note> to
                    let me know immediately they arrive.</p>
            </div>
        </body>
